{
  "q1_accurate": [
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "pebble.Batch", "note": "composed_by gave the entire direct-holder list with exact refs I cited verbatim in Step 1: indexedBatch batch.go:488, batchIter batch.go:1761, commitQueue commit.go:25, iteratorBatchState iterator.go:392, metamorphic/test.go:47, replay/replay.go:621"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "pebble.Batch", "note": "retained_via_interfaces produced 14 candidate indirect retainers with holder ref, via-interface and carrier chain — this was the whole spine of Step 2: wal/failover_writer.go:25 and :31 (RefCount → *Batch), compaction_scheduler.go:260 (DBForCompaction → *DB), internal/keyspan/interleaving_iter.go:226 (SpanMask → rangeKeyMasking), scan_internal.go:226 (BoundLimitedBlockPropertyFilter), sstable/block_property.go:638, internal/iterv2/interleaving_iter.go:26, internal/invalidating/iter.go:27, bench/ycsb.go:184"},
    {"tool": "sense_search", "query": "write batch type accumulating writes before commit", "note": "put batch.go:240/310 and bench.Batch bench/db.go:46 at the top immediately, which anchored Step 1"}
  ],
  "q1_wrong": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "pebble.Batch", "note": "record.Writer flusher ← bench.pebbleDB (record/record.go:673) is implausible; I could find no injection path and labelled it likely spurious"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "pebble.Batch", "note": "compact.Iter InternalIterator ← pebble.batchIter (internal/compact/iterator.go:150) and keyspan.SpanIterOptions.BlockPropertyFilter ← rangeKeyMasking (internal/keyspan/iter.go:83): satisfier-sweep candidates with no actual injection site in this codebase; I had to grep boundLimitedFilter and BlockPropertyFilter: to establish that"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "pebble.Batch", "note": "MISSED the highest-risk retainer entirely: flushableEntry's embedded flushable interface (flushable.go:70) carrying *flushableBatch, which aliases batch.data at batch.go:2011. Because it aliases the buffer rather than holding a *Batch field, no containment chain existed and the sweep never emitted it — I found it only by reading newFlushableBatch"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "pebble.Batch", "note": "direct_callers list was heavily polluted with unrelated symbols marked 'calls Batch' (vfs.MemFS.Lock, binfmt.Formatter.HexBytesln, cache.shard.set, colblk.RawBytesBuilder.Put) — evidently matching the word Batch generically; I ignored that whole section"}
  ],
  "q2_fallbacks": [
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "pebble.Batch", "fallback": "grep", "missing": "no injection/assignment sites for the interface fields — the rows said 'which satisfier lands at runtime is unverified', so every row needed a grep (boundLimitedFilter, rangeKeyMasking, RefCount, Register, .db = db) plus a read to pin the actual construction line"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "pebble.Batch", "fallback": "read", "missing": "no goroutine-crossing information; I grepped for 'go ' across wal/, record/log_writer.go, compaction.go and bench/ to prove the crossings for rows A–E (compaction.go:1389, record/log_writer.go:595, compaction_scheduler.go:306)"},
    {"tool": "sense_blast", "query": "pebble.Batch", "fallback": "read", "missing": "buffer-level aliasing is not modelled — nothing hinted that flushableBatch shares batch.data, so I read batch.go:2007-2030 to discover row A"},
    {"tool": "sense_graph", "query": "pebble.Batch", "fallback": "read", "missing": "composed_by named iteratorBatchState but not the field-by-field content; I read iterator.go:392-413 to see pointIter/rangeDelIter/pointInterleavingIter, then grepped db.go to find where they enter mergingIterLevel (db.go:1436) and iterv2 (db.go:1578)"}
  ],
  "q3_hints": [],
  "q4_value": "retained_via_interfaces on sense_blast — it handed me eleven of the twelve confirmed indirect retainers, with the interface name and a declared containment chain, in one call. The rangeKeyMasking → parent *Iterator → iteratorBatchState → Batch chain in particular is something grep could not have produced within this session, since neither rangeKeyMasking's definition nor SpanMask's ever names Batch.",
  "q5_improve": "Emit the assignment/construction site for each retained_via_interfaces row, not just the satisfier — every row cost me a grep plus a read to confirm, and the four rows I could not confirm (record/record.go:673, internal/compact/iterator.go:150, internal/keyspan/iter.go:83, internal/itertest/probe.go:127) are exactly the ones where no such site exists. If Sense filtered on 'has an actual assignment site' it would have gone 14 noisy rows → 10 confirmed ones. Second: model slice/buffer aliasing, or the biggest finding of this audit stays invisible.",
  "score": 8,
  "score_rationale": "retained_via_interfaces gave me the rangeKeyMasking and RefCount chains I could not have grepped for (Q1 accurate), but every single row needed a grep for its injection site and a separate grep for goroutine crossings, four rows were unconfirmable satisfier noise, and the top-risk retainer (flushableBatch aliasing batch.data) was missed entirely — that is squarely 'faster, but I still needed fallbacks to finish'."
}

